Albuterol inhaler prescribed.  This is a rescue inhaler to be used 1-2 puffs every 4-6 hours to open your airway and relieve acute wheezing.  This medicine does not need to be used like clockwork, it is only as needed when you have wheezing, coughing, or chest tightness.  For more detail on how to properly use beyond our description, please search "metered dose inhaler instructions" on youtube.